>).\r\n\r\nAs the American economist Larry Summers once said, “<em>Most investors want to do today what they should have done yesterday.”</em>\r\n\r\nIt’s time to start trading and practising! Download TradeHero version 1.4 today.','Updates in Version 1.4','','inherit','closed','open','','88-revision-11','','','2013-06-18 11:30:35','2013-06-18 03:30:35','',88,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/88-revision-11',0,'revision','',0),(227,4,'2013-06-18 11:22:34','2013-06-18 03:22:34','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tutr.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-247\" alt=\"tutr\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tutr.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis tutorial introduces to you the basic features of TradeHero. If you are a new user, this will be an advisable place to start the ball rolling by understanding what TradeHero is. If you are an existing user, you may also find this tutorial useful as a refresher.\r\n\r\nFirstly, what is TradeHero? To cut the story short, we bring TradeHero to you in 3 parts:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Learn to Trade</strong></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Earn Money</strong></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3><strong>Follow Experts</strong></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFor more details, refer to our main website here: <a href=\"www.tradehero.mobi\">TradeHero</a><em> </em>\r\n\r\nTo facilitate better and effective learning, we have broken down the main features into details. By reading through the tutorial, we hope to clarify any doubts concerning the usability of the application, as well as to give an overview of what exactly is happening as you use TradeHero. <!--more-->\r\n<h2><strong>1. Profile Screen</strong></h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-3.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-250\" alt=\"image (3)\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-3.png\" width=\"327\" height=\"580\" /></a>\r\n\r\nYour profile screen displays the returns on your portfolio of stocks, the users paying to follow your trades and comments, as well as your performance ranking on different leaderboards.\r\n\r\nYou can tap on the center action button to open up more options.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The <strong>+ </strong>symbol to   buy shares</li>\r\n	<li>The <strong>-</strong>  button to sell shares</li>\r\n	<li>The  <strong>speech</strong>  symbol to post comments. Comments will be sent to your followers and will also appear on your timeline. You are also given options to share your comments on Twitter, Facebook and LinkedIn.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong style=\"font-size: 1.5em;\">2. Community</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/1community.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-229\" alt=\"1community\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/1community.png\" width=\"318\" height=\"402\" /></a>\r\n\r\nFind top traders in the leaderboards, ranked either by raw P&amp;L or by our custom Hero quotient ranking algorithm. You can filter by stock exchange, industry sectors, monthly and quarterly returns and Most Skilled traders.\r\n\r\nAlso, you can compete with your friends on the Friends Leaderboard. How so? By connecting accounts from Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn to see how you stack up amongst your friends.\r\n<h2><strong>3. Portfolio</strong></h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/position.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-232\" alt=\"position\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/position.png\" width=\"320\" height=\"496\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis screen details your current portfolio of stocks: open positions are shown at the top. Closed positions are displayed below. You can tap on the names of stocks to view more details about your positions. Also, you can tap on the right arrows to see the trade history for each position.\r\n<h2><strong>4. Followers </strong></h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/followers.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-230\" alt=\"followers\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/followers.jpg\" width=\"328\" height=\"482\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis screen displays the total number of followers and money you earned from them since you joined TradeHero. Drill down each follower’s name to see the revenue history.\r\n<h2><strong>5. Heroes</strong></h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-5.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-251\" alt=\"image (5)\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-5-576x1024.png\" width=\"332\" height=\"590\" /></a>\r\n\r\nTo follow a hero, 1 TH credit will be deducted per month. Following a Hero will give you instant push notifications whenever the Hero makes a trade or a comment.\r\n\r\nYou will also receive s TradeHero Market Digest email, detailing all the trades and commentary made by the Hero over a weekly or monthly period.\r\n\r\nActive heroes are users you are currently following and paying for. Inactive heroes are users that you have stopped paying for.\r\n<h2><strong>6. Leaderboards</strong></h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/Leaderboatd.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-231\" alt=\"Leaderboatd\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/Leaderboatd.png\" width=\"328\" height=\"552\" /></a>\r\n\r\nLeaderboards rank the performance of individual users worldwide, make more trades and fight to reach the top of the leaderboard to gain followers!\r\n\r\nTo expand your options, you can tap on the names of the users. You can also view the user’s previous closed positions to find out how he reached his current profit level, but to view the user’s current open positions and receive push notifications when the user makes trades and comments,  you will have to tap Follow User and subscribe to him.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe have just introduced the basic features of TradeHero and what we have to offer. Do look out for our next few tips and tutorials where we will explain more on how to<strong><a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/tutorial-part-two-buy-and-sell\"> Buy and Sell Stocks</a> </strong>on TradeHero. Visit our Facebook page for updates and stock tips as well at <a href=\"http://facebook.com/TradeHero\">TradeHero</a>!  Stay tuned!','Tutorial Part One: Introduction','','publish','closed','open','','tutorial-part-one-introduction','','','2013-07-05 12:02:57','2013-07-05 04:02:57','',0,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/?p=227',0,'post','',0),(228,4,'2013-06-19 11:59:10','2013-06-19 03:59:10','This tutorial will introduce to you the basic functions of TradeHero. If you are a new user, this will be a good place to start the ball rolling by understanding what we offer to you. If you are an existing user, you may find this tutorial useful to refresh what you already know about us.\n\nFirstly, what is TradeHero? To cut the story short, we bring TradeHero to you in 3 parts:\n<ul>\n	<li>Learn to Trade</li>\n	<li>Earn Money</li>\n	<li>Follow Experts</li>\n</ul>\nFor more details, refer to our main website at www.tradehero.mobi!\n\nThe application offers a few main functions, and it will be broken down and explained in detail as we go along.\n\n1. Profile Screen\n\nYour profile screen displays the returns on your portfolio of stocks, the users paying to follow your trades and comments, as well as your performance ranking on different leaderboards. Scroll down to see your TradeHero timeline.\n\nTap on the center action button to open up more options. You can tap the + symbol to buy shares, - button to sell shares, and the speech symbol to post comments. Comments will be sent to your followers and will also appear on your timeline.\n\n2. Community\n\nFind top traders in the leaderboards, ranked either by raw P&amp;L or by our custom Hero quotient ranking algorithm. You can filter by stock exchange, industry sectors, monthly and quarterly returns and overall top traders.\n