esting pointed out, top traders are currently ranked only by ROI.  In next version, traders will be ranked by their skill – we have developed a special algorithm to determine this.\r\n\r\nLike how TradeHero sounds? Try it out for yourself! You can download it from the App Store here (<a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/tradehero-mobile/id572226383?ls=1&amp;mt=8\">https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/tradehero-mobile/id572226383?ls=1&amp;mt=8</a>).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Blog Reviews','','inherit','closed','open','','130-revision-14','','','2013-06-20 12:01:53','2013-06-20 04:01:53','',130,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/130-revision-14',0,'revision','',0),(291,4,'2013-06-20 12:02:47','2013-06-20 04:02:47','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/productfinal.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-209\" alt=\"productfinal\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/productfinal.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWe’ve released our newest update on the Apple App Store! View it here: <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/sg/app/tradehero-mobile/id572226383?mt=8\">https://itunes.apple.com/sg/app/tradehero-mobile/id572226383?mt=8</a>.\r\n\r\nNew features include:\r\n\r\n<strong>Most Skilled Leaderboard</strong>: Our new custom algorithm selects only the best and most skilled traders,making it easier for you to find and follow top Quality heroes.\r\n\r\n<strong>Stock Alerts</strong>: Get instant notifications when a stock hits your target price or moves by a desired percentage. Tap the Add Alert button on the stock screen.\r\n\r\n<strong>People search</strong>: The updated search bar now allows you to look up users by name\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nTell us what you think about our update by commenting here, tweeting @TradeHeroMobile, posting on Facebook (<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/TradeHero\">www.facebook.com/TradeHero</a>) or writing to us (<a href=\"mailto:support@tradehero.mobi\">support@tradehero.mobi</a>).\r\n\r\nAs the American economist Larry Summers once said, “<em>Most investors want to do today what they should have done yesterday.”</em>\r\n\r\nIt’s time to start trading and practising! Download TradeHero version 1.4 today.','Updates in Version 1.4','','inherit','closed','open','','88-revision-13','','','2013-06-20 12:02:47','2013-06-20 04:02:47','',88,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/88-revision-13',0,'revision','',0),(292,4,'2013-06-18 11:30:31','2013-06-18 03:30:31','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/wwelcome.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-182\" alt=\"wwelcome\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/wwelcome.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\r\n\r\nToday marks the 6th month since the launch of our application on the 12<sup>th</sup> of December, 2012!\r\n\r\nOn this blog, we’ll be posting updates, stock market news &amp; tips, articles, information on TradeHero and much more. Check it out regularly for the latest news.<!--more-->\r\n\r\nWe’ve had an incredible 6 months. TradeHero’s up for its 2<sup>nd</sup> round of seed funding. Investors have generously responded and we’re on the right track. We’ve been contacted by people from all over the globe telling us that they love this app. If you’ve enjoyed our app so far, rate it on the App Store or let us know on Facebook (<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/TradeHero\">www.facebook.com/TradeHero</a>), Twitter (@TradeHeroMobile) or email us (<a href=\"mailto:support@tradehero.mobi\">support@tradehero.mobi</a>).\r\n\r\nThat said, if you have some improvements in mind, feel free to contact us as well. We’ve received some great feedback along the way that has helped us tremendously. We know that some of you have asked us to include your local stock exchanges (Mexico and India, we hear you!) Don’t worry; we’re on it. We’re excited about the release of our Android version too!\r\n\r\nBehind every Trade Hero are the unsung heroes, the team from Singapore that has been working tirelessly to bring you this application. Our team in Singapore has largely expanded from 2 in early 2012, comprising Dinesh (our CEO) and Dominic (our CTO), to nearly 10 people now.\r\n\r\nPeter Lynch once said, “Owning stocks is like having children - don\'t get involved with more than you can handle.”\r\n\r\nTradeHero has, hopefully, come to the rescue.\r\n\r\nThat’s all for now – stay tuned for updates!','Welcome to TradeHero’s Official Blog','','inherit','closed','open','','86-revision-7','','','2013-06-18 11:30:31','2013-06-18 03:30:31','',86,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/86-revision-7',0,'revision','',0),(293,4,'2013-06-20 13:20:24','2013-06-20 05:20:24','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tipofthweek.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-203\" alt=\"tipofthweek\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tipofthweek.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWhat do you actually know about investment? Have you been making the right choices? This week, we bring the fundamentals of investing to you. We believe that getting the foundation right sets the path for a better investing journey. Are you ready?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFirstly, before you even start to think about ways to invest, set your <strong>motivation</strong> right with the following questions:\r\n\r\nThe <strong>WHY</strong> - Why do you want to invest? Do you have a specific goal? Be it retirement, expenses, education and more, you should have a purpose for your investment. People often start off with the wrong motivation.\r\n\r\nThe <strong>WHAT</strong> - What are you going to do with the money? Planning for the future is always the better choice. Be careful not to spend your profits carelessly,\r\n\r\nThe <strong>HOW</strong> - How much are you willing to risk? How long are you willing to invest? How much do you have to invest without jeopardizing your income? These are common questions that everyone should keep in mind even before stepping into the world of investment.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Think, and plan, and think again. </strong></h2>\r\nOften enough, people do reckless actions that they tend to regret. Like what Warren Buffet says, after you think, think again, if he is unable to list many reasons to buy a stock, it\'s a no-go for him. Do research on the market, read books from best investors in the market, and think hard.\r\n\r\nSomething to think and ponder about is <strong>Risk</strong>. What is risk?\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>Risk refers to potential loss. Risks can be numerous or they can be negligible. When beginner investors are considering their investment options they need to understand the sources of risk so they can minimize the risk factors.</em></span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>Interest rate risk. Changes in interest rates can affect bond prices and bond returns.</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>Purchasing power risk. Because inflation eats away at your purchasing power, the rate of inflation should be considered when investing.</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>Market risk. The rise and drop of the general stock market can affect your specific investment.</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>Marketability risk. The ease with which you can sell your investment.</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>Business risk. If issuers have large financial and overhead commitments, the risk of default is increased.</em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>Reinvestment risk. The ability to reinvest your principal and dividend receipts at a desirable rate. </em></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>Price risk. This risk is based on current interest rates and the rate of inflation.</em></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"color: #808080;\">(Taken from <em>http://www.crown.org/Library/ViewArticle.aspx?ArticleId=431</em>)</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Practice</strong> before you start.</h2>\r\nThis is a very important step. I mean, everyone knows that practice makes perfect. Although there is no perfection in stock investment, but with practice comes familiarity, and with that, you will have a better gauge at the big picture. Before dealing with the real deal, why not get some experience and confirm your trading abilities? Learn and practice how to buy and sell stocks, profits or loss, dividends..etc. And this is what we can help you with. ;)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Keep u<strong>p to date</strong>.</h2>\r\nHave a list of investing websites that you can keep updated with. Follow the trends, latest news about the market, and ensure you know what is going on. Here are a few good investing and market websites for a start:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>http://marketwatch.com</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>http://fool.com</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>http://wikinvest.com</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>http://www.ft.com/home/uk</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAnd the list goes on. This will allow you to choose and monitor which stock to follow, and for a start, try to choose stocks with proven profitabilities with some earnings.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Persevere</strong>.</h2>\r\nSome days, or weeks even, you may find yourself encountering with a bad market, or a bad situation. Avoid performing reckless decisions, and hold on to the stocks. When to hold on to them? <em>\"As long as the fundamentals are still sound, do not sell.\"</em> (http://www.wikihow.com/Invest-in-Stocks) However, when do you know that it\'s time to sell? When the fundamentals are no longer the same and there has been major changes in the company that affects its profits. Another time to let it go is when \"<em>stock price appreciates too much above its value</em>\".\r\n\r\nOne tip from WikiHow is you should consider selling when the price has a significant increase, 50% to 300% depending on the quality of the stock.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Do it yourself.</strong></h2>\r\n<strong> </strong>Try as much to avoid getting stock information or tips from anyone. Do your own research, because often enough, people are getting paid to deliver such tips, and you do not want to fall into such traps that easily. Focus on a goal that you have set for yourself (<em>Tip 1</em>), be it 5 years, 10, or even 20 years. If need be, consult reputable bankers, brokers or advisers for tips on investing properly, and learn from the experts on the aspects of investment.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFrom these simple guidelines, we hope you will be able to have a smooth sailing investment journey from the start. These are not rigid guidelines but simply advice that we feel are essential and good to know as part of the learning process. Investing is not easy, but with proper fundamentals, it can lead to a great success. Have a good investing week!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nInformation was compiled from various websites and credits go to them:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>http://www.crown.org/Library/ViewArticle.aspx?ArticleId=431</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>http://www.wikihow.com/Invest-in-Stocks</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/8-online-investing-websites-improve-gains/</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;','Tip of the Week: How to Invest','','inherit','closed','open','','191-revision-20','','','2013-06-20 13:20:24','2013-06-20 05:20:24','',191,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/191-revision-20',0,'revision','',0),(342,4,'2013-06-26 18:26:43','2013-06-26 10:26:43','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tipofthweek.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-203\" alt=\"tipofthweek\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tipofthweek.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWhat do you actually know about investment? Have you been making the right choices? This week, we bring the fundamentals of investing to you. We believe that getting the foundation right sets the path for a better investing journey. A