en','','','','','2013-06-21 16:53:12','2013-06-21 08:53:12','',0,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/?p=317',0,'post','',0),(318,4,'2013-06-21 16:52:25','2013-06-21 08:52:25','','How to Choose A Stock: Technical Analysis','','inherit','closed','open','','317-revision','','','2013-06-21 16:52:25','2013-06-21 08:52:25','',317,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/317-revision',0,'revision','',0),(319,4,'2013-06-21 17:17:27','2013-06-21 09:17:27','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tut3.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-268\" alt=\"tut3\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tut3.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\n\nIn this tutorial, we will be showing you a step-by-step process on how to Buy and Sell a stock. Although it may seem simple given that the procedures are easy, it takes more than just steps in the trading world. In order to maximise your experience,we suggest looking beyond this tutorial after you grasp a basic understanding of the application.\n<h2><strong>How to Buy/Sell a stock using TradeHero:</strong></h2>\n1. In the buy/sell screen, select a name of the stock. Use the search engine to search for stocks the supported exchanges. You can search by company or symbol name.\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/buysell.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-257\" alt=\"buysell\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/buysell.png\" width=\"354\" height=\"551\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n2.  Use the charts and information provided on the screen to view market data to help you in deciding whether to buy or sell a stock. (T<em>hese information will not be enough, it’s just a guide. You will definitely need more information than that.</em>) Then, use the slider to choose the quantity of stocks that you want to buy. Alternatively, you can use the prefixed amounts found below the slider.\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/APPSTORE3_640x1136_2.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-258\" alt=\"APPSTORE3_640x1136_2\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/APPSTORE3_640x1136_2.png\" width=\"360\" height=\"619\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n3. After clicking the Buy button, you can choose to post comments for reasons to buy or sell the stock. You can also choose to share your buy on your social media feeds like Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn. When you’re done, click on Confirm. And there you go, you have just bought yourself a stock!\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-2.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-259\" alt=\"image (2)\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-2-576x1024.png\" width=\"363\" height=\"645\" /></a>\n\n4.  Similarly, when you want to sell a stock, you can access it through your positions by clicking the middle button and tapping on the <strong>–</strong> button. Then, repeat steps 2 and 3.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBuying and selling a stock isn\'t all that hard once you get the hang of it. Of course, we strongly advise you to do prior research and read up on the actual market before buying or selling a stock. After all, all our data is reflective of the real world and stock market, so why not get more practice to prepare yourself for the real thing? ;)\n\nAnother important function of the application is the <strong>Trade History</strong>.\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-260\" alt=\"image\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-576x1024.png\" width=\"346\" height=\"614\" /></a>\n\nThis screen shows the detailed trade history for a position. You can view the quantity bought or sold, the date and the average price paid after the transaction.\n\n<strong>Realized P&amp;L</strong> is profit or loss banked into your virtual cash after the transaction.\n\n<strong>Unrealised P&amp;L</strong> is the floating profit or loss due to curret market price of the underlying stocks.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong> Stock Alerts</strong>\n\nUsing these information, you will be able to buy and sell a stock on TradeHero easily. Get started! Stay tuned for the last part of our tutorial series, where you will be able to learn <strong>How to Make Real Money</strong> from our application. Til then!\n\n&nbsp;','Tutorial Part Two: Buy and Sell','','inherit','closed','open','','256-revision-14','','','2013-06-21 17:17:27','2013-06-21 09:17:27','',256,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/256-revision-14',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2013-06-24 16:30:34','2013-06-24 08:30:34','','Home-Test','','inherit','closed','open','','320-revision','','','2013-06-24 16:30:34','2013-06-24 08:30:34','',320,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/320-revision',0,'revision','',0),(383,4,'2013-07-31 14:41:37','2013-07-31 06:41:37','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/newsfinaledit.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-406\" alt=\"newsfinaledit\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/newsfinaledit.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\r\n\r\nHello TradeHeroes!\r\n\r\nAs previously mentioned on our <em>Facebook Page (link <a href=\"http://facebook.com/TradeHero\">here</a>)</em>, TradeHero is about to launch a Singapore-based trading competition in early August!(which is really soon!) So, why should you take part in this competition? Well, if you want to stand a chance at winning more than <strong>$30,000</strong> worth of real cash prizes, then you should be a part of this competition! We kid you not, everyone stands an equal chance! Keep looking out for updates here and on our social media platforms, more exciting things are coming soon! Meanwhile, keep practicing and trading!\r\n\r\nThe competition is currently only based in Singapore, but fret not, we\'re looking to offer it to several other countries in the near future!\r\n\r\nIt\'s time to bring out your best trading skills!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/compad2.jpg\"><img cla