ing period.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>1. SILVERSURFER - S$500\r\n2. KELVIN CHUI - S$300\r\n3. HWEE - S$300\r\n4. BERN VIVALA - S$100\r\n5. DRAGNOR - S$100</strong>\r\n\r\nFor users who have missed out, you are still eligible for 2 more weekly prizes of $1,300 and a $5,000 prize pool for monthly prizes, so keep trading!<!--more-->\r\n<div><strong>Top trader makes 29% last week</strong></div>\r\nWithin just one week of the Warrant Hero launch, trader <strong>SILVERSURFER</strong> has made it to the top of the leader board with a 28.5% gain on his warrant portfolio!\r\n\r\n<strong>Top WarrantHero trader takes positions over Hang Seng and China</strong>\r\nSilversurfer entered his first trade on 12 August – the date the WarrantHero game started – with a buy order for <strong><em>HSI call warrant</em></strong> HSI 21600 MB ECW130927 (SP0W), where the underlying Hang Seng futures made a jump more than 350 points or 1.5%, within half an hour.\r\n\r\nThe spike in the Hang Seng was similar to that seen in the <strong><em>China A50 futures</em></strong> on the same day, where Silversurfer also took a bullish position via FTSECHINAA50 7800 MBECW131030 (S3PW). He exited from both positions the next day with a 58.9% on his HSI warrant, and 30% on his China A50 trade. This compares with the 3.7% gain on the HSI futures and 2.8% increase in the China A50 futures over the same period.\r\n\r\nStill bullish on China, Silversurfer re-entered with the same China A50 call warrant on Wednesday. His view this time round however, was wrong and he quickly cut out of this trade with a 19% loss when the futures fell 1.4%.\r\n\r\n<strong>Runner up focuses on Japan index</strong>\r\nFirst runner-up <strong>KELVIN CHUI </strong>also focused on an index warrant – the Nikkei. He was bearish and bought both the shorter-dated Nikkei put NIKKEI225 13500 MB EPW130913 (S9XW) as well as longer-dated NIKKEI225 12500 MB EPW131213 (ST1W). S9XW and ST1W made him 22.1% and 22.6% respectively. The Nikkei futures fe