ication</strong>\r\nHeroes who communicate with their followers regularly about their strategy and market views are more likely to be following the markets closely. They will be able to react and adjust their strategies when faced with new market conditions.\r\n\r\n<strong>7. List the 10 potential heroes to follow</strong>\r\nSelect a proportional mix of traders with low, medium or high risk according to your trading strategy. It helps you create a more balanced portfolio. This will help you when one or two traders are underperforming.\r\n\r\nOne of the biggest mistakes we see users make is not understanding how to analyze signal providers and their trading strategies. For example, users are attracted to traders with 90% winning trades. All they can see is easy and quick profit. But they do not know that the strategy includes a huge risk and when trends go against them, these users might just leave massive open positions in the red.\r\n\r\nKnowing when to cut your losses is always the best skill any trader should have. The same rules apply when it comes to following a Hero. If a Hero is underperforming, not communicating well with followers or taking bigger risks than usual, you should consider these as signs to drop these Heroes.\r\n\r\nNow it is time to find your hero on our <a title=\"TradeHero\" href=\"http://www.tradehero.mobi\">TradeHero mobile</a> application.\r\nLike us on <a title=\"TradeHero Facebook\" href=\"http://www.facebook.com/TradeHero\">Facebook</a>  to get regular updates and news.','7 tips for finding traders to follow on social trading platforms','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-10-31 18:54:56','2013-10-31 10:54:56','',0,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/?p=578',0,'post','',0),(579,1,'2013-10-31 16:07:18','2013-10-31 08:07:18','7 tips for finding traders to follow on social trading platforms\n\nBesides the increase in information shared among users of social trading platforms, the biggest advantage for users of social trading platforms is 